  "title": "Peptic ulcer",
  "body_html": "<b>Peptic ulcer disease (PUD) key points</b><br /><ul><li>Peptic ulcers are common: effect 10% of the population</li><li>Peptic ulcers refer to ulceration of the stomach and duodenum</li><li>Peptic ulcer defined as erosion >5mm diameter</li><li>Ulcers occur when the balance between digestive enzymes and mucosal defences is lost.</li></ul><br /><b>Aetiology</b><br /><ul><li>H.pylori (70-80% of gastric ulcers and >90% of duodenal ulcers are H.pylori related)</li><li>NSAIDs other main cause</li><li>Other causes are: smoking, alcohol, drugs e.g. steroids, stress e.g. burns, autoimmune causes e.g. Crohns, tumours e.g. Zollinger-Ellison syndrome and gastric cancer</li></ul><br /><b>Complications</b><br /><ul><li>Bleeding: peptic ulcer disease most common cause upper GI bleed. </li><li>Perforation: 20% of patients with PUD will perforate</li></ul><br /><b>Site</b><br /><ul><li>Most common site of perforation is anterior wall of the 1st part of duodenum</li><li>Most common site of significant bleeding is posterior wall of the 1st part of duodenum where ulcer erodes gastroduodenal artery</li></ul></div>\n\n<div id=\"mybodylinks\"><table style='width:100%'><tr><td>RCEM learning</td><td style = \"float: right;width:115px;\"><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_like_60\" data-linkid=\"60\" data-rating=\"1\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-up\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_good_count_60\" class = \"link_good_count\" style=\"color:green; font-size:85%;\">1</span><button type=\"button\" style=\"\" id=\"link_dislike_60\" data-linkid=\"60\" data-rating=\"0\" class=\"rate-link btn btn-link\"><svg class=\"bi bi-hand-thumbs-down\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-hand-thumbs-down\"/></svg></button><span id=\"link_bad_count_60\" class = \"link_bad_count\" style=\"color:red; font-size:85%;\">0</span></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\"><a target=\"_b